   Current:  Codex (100% success, 0 vendor bugs)

   To switch back: miniforge config backend claude"}

 :safety-guardrails
 {:automatic-workaround-application
  {:safe-to-auto-apply
   ["Settings file modifications (with backup)"
    "Environment variable changes"
    "Backend switches (reversible)"]
   :require-user-approval
   ["Shell command execution"
    "File deletions"
    "System-wide changes"]
   :always-backup
   ["Config files before modification"
    "Settings before workaround application"
    "Store previous backend in rollback registry"]}

  :backend-switching
  {:conditions
   ["Backend health < 90% success rate"
    "≥ 3 agent-backend errors in 10-minute window"
    "Alternative backend available with > 95% health"]
   :prevent-thrashing
   ["Min 30 minutes between switches"
    "Max 3 switches per hour"
    "Exponential backoff if alternatives also fail"]
   :user-notification
   ["Always notify user of backend switch"
    "Show health metrics for transparency"
    "Provide rollback command"]}}

 :complexity-boundaries
 {:what-to-implement
  ["✅ Workaround detection and application"
   "✅ Backend health tracking"
   "✅ Auto-switch to alternative backends"
   "✅ Registry of known workarounds"
   "✅ User approval for risky workarounds"]

  :what-not-to-implement
  ["❌ Complex pattern avoidance heuristics"
   "❌ ML-based failure prediction"
   "❌ Automatic issue filing on new errors"
   "❌ Cross-backend query routing"
   "❌ Dynamic workaround generation"]

  :rationale
  "Keep it simple:
   1. Detect known problems → apply known solutions
   2. Track reliability → switch when unreliable
   3. No complex heuristics or predictions
   4. User remains in control with transparency"}

 :configuration
 {:config-keys
  {:self-healing-enabled "default: true"
   :workaround-auto-apply "default: true (for safe workarounds)"
   :backend-auto-switch "default: true"
   :backend-health-threshold "default: 0.90 (90% success)"
   :backend-switch-cooldown-ms "default: 1800000 (30 minutes)"
   :workaround-registry-path "~/.miniforge/known_workarounds.edn"
   :backend-health-path "~/.miniforge/backend_health.edn"}

  :user-override
  "# Disable self-healing entirely:
   miniforge config set self-healing.enabled false

   # Require approval for all workarounds:
   miniforge config set self-healing.auto-apply false

   # Disable backend auto-switching:
   miniforge config set self-healing.backend-auto-switch false

   # Adjust health threshold (stricter):
   miniforge config set self-healing.health-threshold 0.95"}

 :testing-strategy
 {:unit-tests
  ["Test workaround detection from mock GitHub issues"
   "Test workaround parsing (extract commands/settings)"
   "Test health calculation from metrics"
   "Test backend selection (choose best alternative)"]

  :integration-tests
  ["Simulate agent-backend error → workaround applied"
   "Simulate repeated failures → backend switched"
   "Test backup creation before workaround"
   "Test rollback when workaround fails"
   "Test cooldown prevents thrashing"]}

 :acceptance-criteria
 [{:criterion "Known workarounds auto-applied"
   :verification "Hit classifyHandoffIfNeeded error, workaround applied automatically"}

  {:criterion "Backend switches when unhealthy"
   :verification "Force Claude failures, system switches to Codex"}

  {:criterion "User notified transparently"
   :verification "Messages show health metrics, workaround details, backend switch reason"}

  {:criterion "Risky operations require approval"
   :verification "Shell commands prompt user before execution"}

  {:criterion "Backups created and restorable"
   :verification "Settings backed up before modification, can be restored"}

  {:criterion "System doesn't thrash"
   :verification "Cooldown prevents rapid backend switching"}]

 :success-metrics
 ["Zero manual intervention for known vendor bugs"
  "< 1% downtime due to vendor issues with known workarounds"
  "Automatic recovery from backend failures"
  "User informed but not interrupted"
  "System resilience increases over time as workaround registry grows"]

 :future-enhancements
 [:community-workaround-sharing
  "Share workaround registry across miniforge users
   → If one user discovers workaround, all benefit"

  :vendor-notification
  "Automatically post health metrics to vendor issue trackers
   → Pressure vendors to fix bugs affecting miniforge"

  :multi-backend-consensus
  "For critical operations, query multiple backends and use consensus
   → If Claude fails but Codex succeeds, trust Codex result"

  :circuit-breaker-pattern
  "After N failures, temporarily disable backend completely
   → Prevent wasted tokens on known-failing backends"]

 :notes
 ["This makes miniforge anti-fragile: it gets stronger from failures"
  "Workaround registry becomes institutional knowledge"
  "Backend health tracking provides vendor accountability"
  "Simple rules > complex heuristics (avoid over-engineering)"
  "User transparency and control maintained throughout"
  "With 6 backends now available, failover is practical"]}
